  static const String shareTxt = 'CLASH OF CARDZ is a highly addictive high score competitive trump card style game. Join the game now and beat others.';
  static const String aboutGameText1 = 'The benefits of play go far beyond fun. True for every group in society. Read on to see how playing cards & board games bring people together.';
  static const String aboutGameText2Header = 'HOW CHILDREN LEARN ABOUT RELATIONSHIPS';
  static const String aboutGameText3 = 'Playing is how children learn from the youngest age. Have you ever seen a baby giggle when you play the easiest game of hide and seek—now you see me, now you don’t? It’s not only adorable: it teaches young brains about the world and the most important people in their lives.';
  static const String aboutGameText4 = 'Through games, children learn to understand the rules of how to treat each other. They figure out what is fair and what is not, and learn about losing and winning together. Playing with others teaches kids about teamwork and strategy. Meanwhile, they are picking up invaluable social skills and, most importantly, making friends for life. All of this comes naturally to children, who can turn any moment.';
  static const String aboutGameText5Header = '… AND WHY WE STILL PLAY AS ADULTS';
  static const String aboutGameText6 = 'When we grow up, does playing still matter? Absolutely. Playtime may not be an essential part of our days as adults, but we keep finding time for fun and games. Be it as structured and planned as getting together for an evening of card or board games with friends, or as simple as pulling a prank on someone in the office: playing games is for all ages.';
  static const String aboutGameText7Header = 'PLAYING CONNECTS US ALL';
  static const String aboutGameText8 = 'Setting up a game is a great way to spend time with friends and family, share laughter and relax. What’s more, games can bring people together in a way that nothing else can. That is why many businesses use games for teambuilding, and why playing a game is the quickest way to break the ice with a group of strangers. Games can convince grandma to get down on the floor with an enthusiastic toddler, and can show you common ground with someone you’ve only just met.';
  static const String aboutGameText9 = 'That brings us back to that Plato quote: “You can discover more about a person in an hour of play than in a year of conversation.” Chances are that Plato never actually said this. He may not even have believed it—his work indicates that he thought games were a bit frivolous.';

